{
  "stem": "9168.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So an uncle and an aunt that I knew and had met, I never really knew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was a-- a non-practicing, if you will, Southern Baptist.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother was Catholic-- Roman Catholic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so my father would not allow my mother to have me baptized at birth in the Catholic church.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was not until I was a teenager, actually, not long before his death, that-- that I was baptized.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I went to two public schools.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went to Baptist Sunday schools in my very, very young life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in high school, in Woodstock, Illinois, I went to a Catholic church, but I never attended any Catholic schools.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, when I was 17.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He became such a serious alcoholic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Severe alcohol like that, he-- by that time we were living in Woodstock, Illinois, just a small town-- 6,000 people-- just an hour and a 1/2 northwest of Chicago.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was then a chef at-- at what was then called an old people's home, in Woodstock.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I've lost my thought there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was at-- when I was 17, that he killed himself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he had been-- it was a little town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- my mother, when life was very difficult, would call the local police.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would just come and pick him up and put him in the jail there to sober up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was pretty much-- he was literally the town drunk-- and the only one.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at this one time, he was-- it was an evening-- and he-- well, they took him out of his cell to play poker with them-- the fire chief, the police chief, somebody else there, and my father.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
